# Memory Bank Protocol

At the start of every new tiltytable session, read all files in `design/memory-bank/` in this order:

1. `projectbrief.md`
2. `productContext.md`
3. `systemPatterns.md`
4. `techContext.md`
5. `activeContext.md`
6. `progress.md`

## When To Update

After substantive work, update:

- `activeContext.md` — current focus and recent decisions
- `progress.md` — completed work and next steps
- Other files only when project fundamentals change

## Rules

- Keep entries concise and factual.
- Do not add extra memory-bank files beyond the six canonical files.
- Project root for app/docs/memory-bank is the **tiltytable repo**; design site lives under `design/`.
- Preserve Vertical Actuator dense-grid rules vs Horizontal Actuator sim-driven grid rules.
- Hardware/runtime truth lives in `.cursor/rules/hardware-*.mdc` and Jetson bring-up notes in `activeContext.md` — do not let design-only memory bank contradict those.
